			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Soloing in the 40's (General Guide to Spirocs in TD)<a name="47046"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jun 19 04 10:03 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span><u>Here are some basics before we get started</u>
<br />

<br />
1)  <b>PAY ATTENTION TO THE RACE, NOT THE FINISH LINE</b>.  20 Mobs at 10% health are just as dangerous as 20 Mobs at 100% health.  In other words, AOE'ing is boring, it takes a while, but you have to pay attention the entire kite.  A missed note and selo's dropping that you're not ready for after you've been kiting for 10 mins really sucks.
<br />

<br />
2)  If you miss a note on a damage spell (DDD or COD), don't recast it.  Go back to Selos and start the whole twist over.  The RNG is funny, if I miss a note starting DDD, it seems like i'm more likely to miss a note on selo's.  I would rather miss one round of damage then have to deal with speed running out.
<br />

<br />
3)  Autocircle is fine, but at least learn how to kite without it.
<br />

<br />
<u>OK, Now for the Spirocs</u>
<br />
Read everything you can in the Guides section, lots of useful information.
<br />

<br />
1)  Couldn't fine the post again when I started typing this, but I read somewhere that kiting Spirocs wasn't as much fun because of the long run to get there.  Translocator in BB to TD, long run north over the water, hit the deserted Island, then the spiroc Island is next one to the west.  I made that trip many times until I get smarter.
<br />

<br />
***There is a translocater in OASIS that takes you straight to the Spirocs Island, you land on the far side of the Island with the ogres, but so far I've had not had any aggro me on zone iin.  Bind in North or South ro, short trip to Oasis if you die.  Much much easier then running over the water with no gear.
<br />

<br />
2)  I don't like swapping instruments, so I just twist selo's and Agilmente's start at the bottom of the tower and run up.  (This is instead of invising up, running to the top, dropping invis and running down, WHICH IS SO MUCH SAFER, I just perfer doing things the hardway).
<br />

<br />
3) When you first start you're not KOS to the spirocs, so until I started getting them all by running by I did two kites.  Get as many as I could the first time, kill them off, go get the rest.  Now after 5 levels there, I just have to run up and I get them all, it's much faster, but also more dangerous.
<br />

<br />
4)  STAY OFF THE MOUNTAIN AND AWAY FROM THE SPIROC WARRIORS.  First time there, i'm looking at track, see a couple of warriors, so I goto add them to my kite, run up the mountain.  I see a spiroc warrior and then a little doggy named spiroc warrior's pet.  They are Shamans and will root you, and you will die if you have a  kite started.
<br />

<br />
5)  I did my circle just south of the tower, there is a large enough open area or to the beach to the east.  Both places are big enough to run around in.
<br />

<br />
6) The lightfoots drop for me when the provens and watchers are about 30%.  Once again don't get careless when you see half your kite dead at 30%, the remaining ones will kill you just as fast.
<br />

<br />
Enjoy it, be prepared to die numerous times, trust me at 45 so far one kite more then makes up double what I lose in exp.  
<br />

<br />
Oh, I was checking on the quest for the workers sledgemallet.  I guess you need good venthril sathir (spelling?) faction.  So don't kill the ogres on the spiroc island, they lower it.  I just hope it won't take me long to get back what i've lost so far.
<br />

<br />
Thanks for reading.
<br />

<br />
Hatan (No surname yet, any ideas)
<br />

<br />

<br />
  
<br />

<br />
</span></td>
