			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Soloing in the 40's (General Guide to Spirocs in TD)<a name="47068"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jun 19 04 2:26 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>First of all, nice guide to the spirocs.
<br />

<br />
But there are two reasons why kiting spirocs is inferior to Dulak's Harbor. Even though the mobs in DH most likely has more hitpoints, there's two things that make spirocs suck:
<br />

<br />
Backstabs. Because of backstabs there are no way in h*ll, you can ever survive a hit from the swarm. All mobs seem to bug gruesomly when you kite them in massive numbers, and if one of them gets in range to hit you and stuns you, the rest are most likely to just stand and watch you get unstunned. Or, at most, scratch away around 1000 hitpoints. But then that's all, you can get right back to kiting them again. The backstabs makes sure you die instantly the nanosecond you're hit.
<br />

<br />
Pulling. Pulling the spirocs is a pain. It really is. There's absolutly no way around that. The armory in DH is a 15 sec pull and you're all set to begin kiting.
<br />

<br />
I've shared a handy technique for kiting in DH, so as early as in the mid-30'ies you can make massive exp in DH instead.
<br />

<br />
And as far as the faction for the workers mallet, you just click on DE illusion and fire up the faction song with a normal flute equipped. The faction hits you take from killing the ogres isn't really gonna mess it all up for you, unless you go on a massive killing spree there...</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
